<br>
One suggestion I can give to all of you, is that the biles should be collected first and you should bring the bile extractor and the coldain tanning kit with you while you are collecting as nothing in this part stacks.  Currently I have 2 glowing silks, 3 biles, 2 fibers, and 4 threads which will be 3 glowing silks and 2 biles oncxe I get one more thread, so it really does save space and is pretty much necassary unless you vacate all your inventory slots.<br>
<br>
Fredre <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 10:37:25 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 5th Shawl Threads</span><hr size=1> Invis up and learn your way to Frenzy and Eyes camps. Threads drop more often up there. If no one else is working on the shawl you can probably get enough to finish this part of the quest in a night or 2. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor Kilbringer</b></a><br>Evoker of the 58th Conclave<br><span style="font-size: 10px">Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b><br>
